Grammar:

Rule 0     S' -> statement
Rule 1     statement -> expr
Rule 2     expr -> FALSE
Rule 3     expr -> TRUE
Rule 4     expr -> expr AND expr  [precedence=left, level=2]
Rule 5     expr -> expr OR expr  [precedence=left, level=1]

Terminals, with rules where they appear:

AND                  : 4
FALSE                : 2
OR                   : 5
TRUE                 : 3
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear:

expr                 : 1 4 4 5 5
statement            : 0


state 0

    (0) S' -> . statement
    (1) statement -> . expr
    (2) expr -> . FALSE
    (3) expr -> . TRUE
    (4) expr -> . expr AND expr
    (5) expr -> . expr OR expr
    FALSE           shift and go to state 3
    TRUE            shift and go to state 4

    statement                      shift and go to state 1
    expr                           shift and go to state 2

state 1

    (0) S' -> statement .


state 2

    (1) statement -> expr .
    (4) expr -> expr . AND expr
    (5) expr -> expr . OR expr
    $end            reduce using rule 1 (statement -> expr .)
    AND             shift and go to state 5
    OR              shift and go to state 6


state 3

    (2) expr -> FALSE .
    AND             reduce using rule 2 (expr -> FALSE .)
    OR              reduce using rule 2 (expr -> FALSE .)
    $end            reduce using rule 2 (expr -> FALSE .)


state 4

    (3) expr -> TRUE .
    AND             reduce using rule 3 (expr -> TRUE .)
    OR              reduce using rule 3 (expr -> TRUE .)
    $end            reduce using rule 3 (expr -> TRUE .)


state 5

    (4) expr -> expr AND . expr
    (2) expr -> . FALSE
    (3) expr -> . TRUE
    (4) expr -> . expr AND expr
    (5) expr -> . expr OR expr
    FALSE           shift and go to state 3
    TRUE            shift and go to state 4

    expr                           shift and go to state 7

state 6

    (5) expr -> expr OR . expr
    (2) expr -> . FALSE
    (3) expr -> . TRUE
    (4) expr -> . expr AND expr
    (5) expr -> . expr OR expr
    FALSE           shift and go to state 3
    TRUE            shift and go to state 4

    expr                           shift and go to state 8

state 7

    (4) expr -> expr AND expr .
    (4) expr -> expr . AND expr
    (5) expr -> expr . OR expr
    AND             reduce using rule 4 (expr -> expr AND expr .)
    OR              reduce using rule 4 (expr -> expr AND expr .)
    $end            reduce using rule 4 (expr -> expr AND expr .)


state 8

    (5) expr -> expr OR expr .
    (4) expr -> expr . AND expr
    (5) expr -> expr . OR expr
    OR              reduce using rule 5 (expr -> expr OR expr .)
    $end            reduce using rule 5 (expr -> expr OR expr .)
    AND             shift and go to state 5
